   <ext_description linkend="Alias_identification_mim.aliases_are_valid">
The <b>aliases_are_valid</b> rule ensures that all instances of <express_ref linkend="identification_assignment:mim:Identification_assignment_mim.applied_identification_assignment"/>

 whose identification role is 'alias',
contain, in their items attribute, only instances of types listed in <express_ref linkend="alias_identification:mim:Alias_identification_mim.aliasable_item"/>.
</ext_description>

   <ext_description linkend="Alias_identification_mim.aliases_are_valid.wr:WR1">
there shall not be any instance of <express_ref linkend="identification_assignment:mim:Identification_assignment_mim.applied_identification_assignment"/>

 that provides an alias to an instance of an entity not listed in <express_ref linkend="alias_identification:mim:Alias_identification_mim.aliasable_item"/>.
</ext_description>
